register.description: This register contains the IP revision code for the SCRM.

bitfield.description: Reads returns 0.
Revision Number

register.description: This register holds the clock setup time counters of the system clock source supplier.

bitfield.description: Reads returns 0.
Holds the number of 32 kHz clock cycles it takes to gate the clock source supplier.
Reads returns 0.
Holds the number of 32 kHz clock cycles it takes to stabilize the clock source supplier.

register.description: This register holds the setup time counters for the sleep mode of the PMIC.

bitfield.description: Reads returns 0.
Holds the number of 32 kHz clock cycles it takes to exit the PMIC from sleep mode.
Reads returns 0.
Holds the number of 32 kHz clock cycles it takes to enter the PMIC in sleep mode.

register.description: This register controls the alternate system clock source supplier.

bitfield.description: Reads returns 0.
This bit allows to enable and disable the output alternate system clock version. This bit is intended to be used in order to gate this clock path while the source is stabilizing.

bitenum.description: The alternate system clock version is disabled.
The alternate system clock version is enabled.

bitfield.description: This bit allows to enable and disable the alternate system clock version used to generate the auxiliary clocks. This bit is intended to be used in order to gate this clock path while the source is stabilizing and also to gate this clock path while switching the auxiliary clock paths on / from this possible source.

bitenum.description: The alternate system clock version is disabled.
The alternate system clock version is enabled.

bitfield.description: This bit field defines the functional mode of the alternate system clock supplier.

bitenum.description: The alternate system clock source supplier is powered-down.
The alternate system clock source supplier is active.
The alternate system clock source supplier is bypassed.

register.description: This register holds the reset time counter which is used to extend the reset lines beyond the release of the pad reset.

bitfield.description: Reads returns 0.
Holds the number of 32 kHz clock cycles for which the reset duration is extended. Values 0,1 and 2 are not allowed. 0x0: Reserved. 0x1: Reserved. 0x2: Reserved.

register.description: This register controls the release of the external C2C interface reset lines.

bitfield.description: Reads returns 0.
This bit allows to release the warm reset line of the external C2C interface. [warm reset sensitive]

bitenum.description: Clearing this bit has for effect to release the warm reset line of the external C2C interface.
Writing this bit has for effect to assert the warm reset line of the external C2C interface.

bitfield.description: This bit allows to release the cold reset line of the external C2C interface.

bitenum.description: Clearing this bit has for effect to release the cold reset line of the external C2C interface.
Writing this bit has for effect to assert the cold reset line of the external C2C interface.

register.description: This register allows the software to perform an external power-on reset.

bitfield.description: Reads returns 0.
This bit controls the assertion and the de-assertion of the external power-on reset.

bitenum.description: De-asserts the external power-on reset.
Asserts the external power-on reset.

bitfield.description: This bit must be set to 1 to allow the software to assert the external power-on reset.

bitenum.description: Prevents the software to assert the external power-on reset.
Allows the software to assert the external power-on reset.

register.description: This register logs the source of warm reset output. Each bit is set upon release of the warm reset output and must be cleared by software.

bitfield.description: Reads returns 0.
This bit logs the external warm reset source.

bitenum.description: No external warm reset occurred.
An external warm reset occurred.

register.description: This register logs the source of warm reset on the APE. Each bit is set upon release of the APE warm reset and must be cleared by software.

bitfield.description: Reads returns 0.
This bit logs the APE warm reset source.

bitenum.description: No APE warm reset occurred.
An APE warm reset occurred.

bitfield.description: Reads returns 0.

register.description: This register logs the source of warm reset on the external C2C interface. Each bit is set upon release of the external C2C interface warm reset and must be cleared by software.

bitfield.description: Reads returns 0.
This bit logs the C2C warm reset source.

bitenum.description: No C2C warm reset occurred.
A C2C warm reset occurred.

bitfield.description: Reads returns 0.
